# Oura API credentials (OAuth2)
#
# Setup instructions:
#   1. Go to https://cloud.ouraring.com and sign in
#   2. Navigate to Developer Portal -> My Applications
#      Direct link: https://cloud.ouraring.com/oauth/applications
#   3. Click "Create Application" and fill in:
#      - App name: Oura Digital Twin (or any descriptive name)
#      - Redirect URI: http://localhost:4421/callback  (must match exactly)
#      - Description: optional
#   4. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret into the fields below
#   5. Run: python api/oura_oauth2_setup.py
#      This opens a browser for OAuth2 authorization and saves tokens
#      to this .env file automatically.
#
# After setup, import_oura.py will use these tokens.
# The refresh token is rotated automatically by the daily pipeline.
#
# Alternative: Personal Access Token (simpler, no OAuth2 flow needed)
#   1. Go to https://cloud.ouraring.com/personal-access-tokens
#   2. Create a token and paste it into OURA_ACCESS_TOKEN below
#   3. Leave OURA_CLIENT_ID and OURA_CLIENT_SECRET empty
#   Note: PATs do not auto-refresh. You must regenerate manually when expired.

# OAuth2 credentials - from Developer Portal -> My Applications
# OURA_CLIENT_ID: The application identifier assigned when you create an app
OURA_CLIENT_ID=
# OURA_CLIENT_SECRET: The secret key shown once at app creation (save it!)
OURA_CLIENT_SECRET=

# OAuth2 tokens (populated automatically by oura_oauth2_setup.py - do not edit manually)
# Can also be set manually with a Personal Access Token (see instructions above)
OURA_ACCESS_TOKEN=
OURA_REFRESH_TOKEN=
